{"type":"message","id":"95a5cc3a","parentId":"587168b8","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:37:03.434Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me read the summarize skill to understand how to use it.","thinkingSignature":"fc7ce4b6a08269d5abe710db09ab3bed98b2294bd5aa0b660a838222c1fd032c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9rvojwf2nge7_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/summarize/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6663,"output":57,"cacheRead":27269,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33989,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777347420898,"responseId":"063f5e5de3ce1e29ff9cb36888741d92"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6928c357","parentId":"95a5cc3a","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:37:03.454Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9rvojwf2nge7_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: summarize\ndescription: Summarize or transcribe URLs, YouTube/videos, podcasts, articles, transcripts, PDFs, and local files.\nhomepage: https://summarize.sh\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\":\n      {\n        \"emoji\": \"🧾\",\n        \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"summarize\"] },\n        \"install\":\n          [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"brew\",\n              \"kind\": \"brew\",\n              \"formula\": \"steipete/tap/summarize\",\n              \"bins\": [\"summarize\"],\n              \"label\": \"Install summarize (brew)\",\n            },\n          ],\n      },\n  }\n---\n\n# Summarize\n\nFast CLI to summarize URLs, local files, and YouTube links.\n\n## When to use (trigger phrases)\n\nUse this skill immediately when the user asks any of:\n\n- “use summarize.sh”\n- “what’s this link/video about?”\n- “summarize this URL/article”\n- “transcribe this YouTube/video” (best-effort transcript extraction; no `yt-dlp` needed)\n\n## Quick start\n\n```bash\nsummarize \"https://example.com\" --model google/gemini-3-flash-preview\nsummarize \"/path/to/file.pdf\" --model google/gemini-3-flash-preview\nsummarize \"https://youtu.be/dQw4w9WgXcQ\" --youtube auto\n```\n\n## YouTube: summary vs transcript\n\nBest-effort transcript (URLs only):\n\n```bash\nsummarize \"https://youtu.be/dQw4w9WgXcQ\" --youtube auto --extract-only\n```\n\nIf the user asked for a transcript but it’s huge, return a tight summary first, then ask which section/time range to expand.\n\n## Model + keys\n\nSet the API key for your chosen provider:\n\n- OpenAI: `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n- Anthropic: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`\n- xAI: `XAI_API_KEY`\n- Google: `GEMINI_API_KEY` (aliases: `GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY`, `GOOGLE_API_KEY`)\n\nDefault model is `google/gemini-3-flash-preview` if none is set.\n\n## Useful flags\n\n- `--length short|medium|long|xl|xxl|<chars>`\n- `--max-output-tokens <count>`\n- `--extract-only` (URLs only)\n- `--json` (machine readable)\n- `--firecrawl auto|off|always` (fallback extraction)\n- `--youtube auto` (Apify fallback if `APIFY_API_TOKEN` set)\n\n## Config\n\nOptional config file: `~/.summarize/config.json`\n\n```json\n{ \"model\": \"openai/gpt-5.2\" }\n```\n\nOptional services:\n\n- `FIRECRAWL_API_KEY` for blocked sites\n- `APIFY_API_TOKEN` for YouTube fallback\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777347423453}}
{"type":"message","id":"72a7ab6c","parentId":"6928c357","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:37:08.368Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I know how to use the summarize tool. Let me transcribe the first video. The video URL is `https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cgp-gfSbmNE`.\n\nI'll use `summarize \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cgp-gfSbmNE\" --youtube auto --extract-only` to get the transcript.\n\nLet me start with the first video.","thinkingSignature":"731fb744e331db62788097f26919cb8f1ecff9db7705cee089bd7ae8ef019d6a"},{"type":"text","text":"Starting on video 1: **\"ChatGPT 5.5 Codex: I can't believe they did this...\"**\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nt21muk4pak4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"summarize \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cgp-gfSbmNE\" --youtube auto --extract-only","timeout":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":7331,"output":162,"cacheRead":27269,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34762,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777347423455,"responseId":"063f5e5f15c7d6ca0512bc868ab1d78b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"58c87a39","parentId":"72a7ab6c","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:37:12.627Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nt21muk4pak4_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Transcript:\nI've been using Chat GPT 5.5 non-stop\nsince it released a few days ago and I'm\nblown away. I figured out a workflow\nthat I'm going to show you in this video\nthat I don't think I've seen anywhere\nelse that will completely change how you\nbuild with AI. I also put it\nhead-to-head with Opus 47 and Claude\ncode in hundreds of tests and I can\nconfidently tell you one of these two\nare better than the other. In this\nvideo, I'll go over what makes Chat GPT\n5.5 so different, why the Codex app is a\ncomplete game-changer, show you my\nmaster workflow for both beginners and\nadvanced, then tell you what you should\nbe using once and for all, Opus 47 and\nClaude code or Chat GPT 5.5 and Codex.\nThis is going to be a banger. Let's lock\nin and get into it. This isn't a channel\nwhere we spend 20 minutes reading blog\nposts, looking at charts, and looking at\nfake benchmark tests. No, we're not\ndoing that. We get straight into the\naction. So, this is Codex. This is the\ndesktop Codex app. This is by far the\nbest way to be using Chat GPT 5.5. I\nbasically spend 90% of my day now inside\nof this app. So, what you need to do\nimmediately is go and download this.\nThey have released so many updates over\nthe last few days to this. It is\nbasically a completely different app.\nSo, if you haven't downloaded and used\nCodex for desktop yet, go ahead, pause\nthis video, do it now. So, everything we\ndo, you can do it with me together. So,\nreal quick, we'll talk about the big\nimprovements I've experienced in Chat\nGPT 5.5. Number one, and this is the\nbiggest improvement in my eyes, takes\naction by default. Chat GPT 5.4, the\nbiggest issue is I tell it to do\nsomething, it doesn't actually do it. I\nhave to sit there and beg on my knees,\n\"Please, Chat GPT 5.4, do what I tell\nyou to do.\" And it wouldn't do it. It\nwas very smart, but not about that\naction. 5.5, slightly less chatty. I\nfelt like I was reading a novel every\ntime I would give 5.4 a prompt. I\nliterally would crash out sometimes and\nsay, \"Please, for the love of God, just\nstop saying so much. Get straight to the\npoint.\" That is not as much of an issue\nwith 5.5. Still a little bit of an\nissue, not as much of an issue. Better\npersonality. 5.4 was a cold Terminator\nmachine. It did not feel warm to talk\nto. It was not quite as fun to talk to.\n5.5, better personality. Not perfect\npersonality, better personality. And a\nbig one here, it is significantly\nsmarter. It creates excellent,\nexcellent, excellent code. I basically,\nover the last few days of testing this,\nhave gotten zero bugs out of the code\nit's written. Zero, zero, zero. So, it\nis much, much, much smarter, which is\namazing to see. Now, these are all big,\ngreat improvements, but I'll tell you\nwhat, the biggest improvement comes from\nthe experience of using it inside this\napp I'm showing you here. This is the\nnew Codex desktop app. You need to do\nyourself a favor. You need to pause this\nvideo immediately. You need to go\ndownload this. Go download the Codex\ndesktop app because this is incredible.\nThis is where I've spent 95% of my\nwaking moments over the last few days is\ninside this app. There are 20,000\ndifferent features that make it amazing\nthat I'll be going through in this\nvideo, but you need to be downloading\nthis immediately. 5.5 with this Codex\napp is\nIt's a match made in heaven. It's a\nbeautiful It's a beautiful harmony of AI\ngenius. So, here's the plan for the\nvideo and here's why you need to buckle\nin immediately. I'm going to build out a\nbasic app using this Codex app. I'm\ngoing to show you how to use it, many\nthe incredible features. Once we got a\ngood feel for the app, we're comfortable\nwith it, we know what it's doing, then\nwe'll go to a super advanced workflow\nthat I promise will change your life. It\nis It's changed everything for me. It's\nhelped me build apps literally, I'm not\neven joking, 10 times better and faster.\nWe'll go into that advanced workflow\nright after we get comfortable with this\nand I go through the strengths of the\nmodel and the app. When we talk about\nChat GPT 5.5, we're also implicitly\ntalking about this app as well just\nbecause they work so well together. So,\ngetting off a few things, let's just do\nquick tour of the app. We'll We'll spend\na couple seconds here. Over on the\nleft-hand side, everything is organized\nby project. You'll see a lot of new\nproject 1 2 3 4 5 over here. That's cuz\nI've been doing insane amounts of tests\nover the last few days. But, what's\ngreat is is you can multitask so easily\nin here. You can start off multiple\nchats in a project, work on the back end\nwhile you're working on the front end,\nwhile you have a chat going where you're\ngame planning the entire app itself.\nThis is a beautiful part about the Codex\napp. Then down below, what's amazing is\nyou can also have chats. So, they've\ncombined into this super app not only\nthe coding section, but also you have a\nchat section. For those who build\nthings, you need to be having chats\nseparate from your building, separate\nfrom your coding. So, as one goes at it,\nas you're coding and building something,\nyou can have a chat going where you're\ndoing high-level planning, design,\ndevelopment, whatever it is, you can\nhave those separate chats going. So, you\ncan strategize and brainstorm on the app\nand business you're building. So, it's\nbeautiful they combined this all in one.\nIn the Claude app, it's very different.\nEverything is separated out. So, you\nhave your chats and then you have to go\nover here and you switch to your code.\nAnd to talk to one or the other, you're\nswitching between these entirely\ndifferent interfaces. You can see even\nthe colors of the background are\ndifferent. It's just completely\ndifferent app. I don't like that\nseparation quite as much. With Codex, it\nis all tightly integrated, which is\nbeautiful. One thing you also want to do\nbefore you start building is go into\nsettings down here. Go into your\nsettings. Go over to computer use and\nmake sure this is turned on. For me, it\nwas off by default. Make sure you turn\nthis on. This is one of the new amazing\nfeatures that they just dropped in here\nwhere it can control your entire\ncomputer. It's clear they're trying to\neat open claw and put it into this Codex\napp. I'm fine with it. You just got to\nmake sure you turn on this computer use\nright here, which will allow Codex to do\na lot of really cool things, including\ntesting your apps, doing different\nthings on your computer. It's all part\nof the super app they're going for. So,\nlet's do this. Let's build out an app.\nAnd as we build out the app, I'll take\nyou around, show you the different\nfeatures, show you all the cool things\ngoing on so you can see what makes this\nmodel so powerful and what makes this\napp so beautiful. So, make sure you go\nup here, you create a new project, put\nit in a new folder. What we're going to\nbe building today is a prompt library\napp. It's an app where you can take your\nbest prompts, the ones you reuse all\noften, and save it. This is great\nbecause after you're done building this\nwith me, you can use it for whatever you\nwant. But, let's do this. One thing you\nneed to know, there's a lot going on\nhere. We've tested it all. I've tested\nlow, medium, high, extra high for\nintelligence. I know it's very tempting\nto do extra high for everything. When\nyou're using Claude code, you use the\nhighest level for everything cuz you\njust get the best results. But, that's\ndifferent here. They made Chat GPT 5.5,\nand this is one of the reasons why it's\na really good model, very intelligent,\nvery efficient with its intelligence.\nSo, you actually don't need to be using\nextra high for everything. That can\nactually be a hindrance in many\nscenarios. So, what you want to do is\nyou actually want to use medium for\neverything. I tested it all. Medium is\nthe sweet spot. You pretty much want to\nuse medium for everything. So, now that\nwe're there, also full access. Instead\nof default permissions, they have to\nclick accept, accept, accept, accept all\nthe time. Just go straight into full\naccess. We've gone past the point of AI\ndoing dangerous things on your computer.\nYou can do full access. It'll make your\nworkflow so much faster. So, let's start\nbuilding this out and we're going to\nstart off right off the rip with what is\none of the most amazing, beautiful\nstrengths of Codex and 5.5 that\ndominates Claude code, and that is the\nintegration\nwith the image to model. For those who\ndon't know, if you've been living under\na rock the last week, OpenAI released\nthe image to model and it is by far and\naway, not even close, the best image\ngeneration model on planet Earth. It\ndestroys Nano Banana. thing here is it\nis completely\nbuilt into Codex. So, let me show you\nhow I do this. Let's get into this\nworkflow and show you some cool things\nyou can do. All right, so here we go.\nTake this prompt. I'll put it down\nbelow. What you're going to see here is\nhow I use the built-in image gen model\nto first come up with an interface. This\nis going to allow us to make much\nbetter, more beautiful interfaces. This\nis again one of the strengths of Chat\nGPT 5.5 with Codex. deeply integrated\nwith that incredible new image gen\nmodel. I want to build a prompt library\napp. By the way, if you do this with me,\nyou'll have an amazing app you can use\nwhenever you want. It'll allow you to go\nand revisit all your most commonly used\nprompts. So, build this with me here.\nThe user should be able to save commonly\nused prompts, to see their library, and\nolder prompts saved. They should be able\nto favorite and organize them. Let's\nmake this a beautiful but simple\ninterface like linear. Please use the\nimage gen model to first generate four\nor five options for this interface. This\nis something Claude code doesn't have.\nThey don't have an image gen model at\nall. Not only does Chat GPT have the\ngreatest image gen model in the world,\nbut it is deeply integrated into Codex.\nSo, let's do this. Also, by the way, you\ncan turn up the speed to fast. Their\nfast model is incredible. And their\nusage they give you is so high that you\nreally can get away with using it a ton.\nSo, I'm going to hit send on this. And\nthe first thing it's going to do is get\nus some interfaces we can look at and\nchoose first. All right, looks like it\nfinished. And look at this, five\ndifferent interfaces for us to choose\nfrom. This is something Claude code\ncannot do because it doesn't have any\nsort of image gen in it. Let's take a\nquick look and choose one. Again, this\nis something you should be doing with\nbasically every app you're building is\ntaking advantage of this incredible\nimage gen model to first figure out what\nyou want your interface to look like.\nOkay, so we got our first one. Looking\nnice, a little busy. I think it's a\nlittle busy. Let's check out the second\none. I like that a little bit better.\nLet's see the third one. Ooh, I like the\ncard style. I think I'm going to go with\nthe card style. Let's just check out\nfour and five here.\nFour, okay. Okay, looking nice. And then\nfive. I think this is the winner.\nGreen's my favorite color. Let's go.\nLet's do this. I'm just going to copy\nthis. I'm going to put it in. I'm going\nto paste it here. I'm going to do this.\nI'm going to say, \"I love the fifth one,\nthe one with the green accents and\ncards. Can we start building the app\nbased on that?\" And I know, I know,\nthere's a click to dictate button.\nEveryone in every video says, \"Hey, why\ndon't you just dictate?\" I like typing.\nI'm a typer. I enjoy typing. So, we're\ngoing to do this. We have it full\naccess. I just do full access for\neverything. I fully trust the model.\nWe're going to keep it on medium, have\nthe speed high, and I'm going to hit\nsend, and it is going to get to work\nhere. What we're going to see as it\nbuilds this out is some of the amazing\nfunctionality that really separates\nChatGPT from any of the other apps or\ntools out there. I can't wait to show\nyou what what happens when we get into\nthe testing part when it comes to\ncomputer use and different things it\ndoes with the built-in browser. Stick\naround for this. I think you're going to\nbe blown away by what it can do. Also,\nas it builds, we're going to get into a\nmuch more advanced workflow after we go\nthrough this. I just want to show you\nall the kind of bells and whistles of\nChatGPT 5.5 with Codex. Then we'll get\ninto super advanced right after. I feel\nlike this is a little bit more fun than\nreading through blog posts, right? I\nfeel like this is a cooler way to do\nthis. And then also, right after that is\nthe big comparison with this in Claude\nCode with the final recommendation. So,\nstick around for that. By the way, if\nyou learned anything at all so far, make\nsure to leave a like down below.\nSubscribe, turn notifications. Coming up\nin the next week, I'll do a live boot\ncamp of Codex inside the Vibe Coding\nAcademy. The link for that is down\nbelow. It's the number one AI community\non planet Earth, so check that out as\nwell. All right, looks like it finished\ngoing. Now, here is some really cool\nstrength of the Codex app with ChatGPT\n5.5. The integrations with so many\ndifferent tools are incredible. So,\nfirst of all, built-in browser. So, you\npop it open and you can immediately see\nit works with this built-in browser. And\nif I even go into full screen mode, you\ncan see a lot more of it. And it\nbasically looks exactly like the image\ngen we got as we were planning this,\nwhich is amazing. But let's look at some\nof the built-in tools here that there's\nbasically no other app on planet Earth\nhas. We can now start editing this app\nstraight from this live browser in\nCodex. So, there's many tools we have\nhere. First of all, we have this\nannotate. So, if I go in here, as you\ncan see as I hover around the app, it\nselects different elements and I can say\nfor it to change different things. So,\nif I want to go in here, let's add a\nfavorites button up here. So, as I'm\nbuilding a new prompt, I can immediately\nput into favorites. So, I put it there\nand I can say, \"Let's add a favorites\nbutton.\" This is one of my favorite ways\nto use ChatGPT 5.5 in Codex is instead\nof just prompting back and forth, I just\ngo straight into the app and I start\nannotating live on the app. It's like\nI'm actually building the app inside the\napp rather than just talking to a\nchatbot. So, I'm going to say this, I'm\ngoing to hit that, I'm going to add it,\nand then I'm going to hit send on that.\nAnd now it's going to get to work. This\nis one of the most fun ways for me to be\nbuilding out my apps. And boom, just\nlike that, there's your favorites\nbutton. It added. I'm not even sending\nprompts. I'm just checking off different\nthings inside the interface. So, that is\nreally, really cool. And now I can go\nback in here and continue editing\nthrough annotations if I want. But let's\ndo this. Let's say we like where the app\nis. Say we want to do testing. There's a\nlot of things here, right? There's a lot\nof things on our screen. We want to get\nit tested, but maybe we got other things\ngoing on. Maybe we're about to eat\nlunch, and when we come back, we want it\nfully tested. So, let's do this. We can\ntake advantage of computer use. This is\nagain something Claude Code does not\nhave. One of the big advantages here is\nCodex can actually use and control your\ncomputer. So, let's do this. Can you use\ncomputer use\nto test all the features of the app? And\nI'm going to hit enter 