But I'm going to say, please build\na dashboard prototype using all these\nassets. What you're going to want to do\nhere is describe your app so it can\nbuild the dashboard out for it or\nwhatever you're building. If you're\nlooking to make a slideshow, you can\ndescribe that. For me, I'm building an\napp. So, I'm going to describe my app\ninto the chat with all of these assets\nin there. And I'm going to hit enter and\nsend. and it's going to take that and it\nis going to start building out that\nprototype. There you go. Now you can see\nit. It's building it out and it is going\nto get to work. So just to recap as it\nbuilds this where we're at so far. We\nbuilt out using Chad GBT image gen all\nusing all our inspiration exactly what\nlogos we wanted, what design direction\nwe wanted. So we didn't have to\nexperiment in claw design. We took all\nthose findings after our exploration and\nrefinement put it into claw design. We\nmade our design system. We had some\nartifacts created. We refined it a\nlittle bit. And now we're building out\nthe prototype, the final stage. And\nlet's see what we're going to get out of\nthis. So, it's building it out right\nnow. We even got our merch design, our\napp logos, all of that. And boom. Just\nlike that, we have our dashboard built\nout. Check that out. We have our\nworkspace. We have a really nice system\nthat shows all the opportunities, active\nruns. If if you're not as familiar with\nHenry intelligent machines, what I'm\nbuilding out, this might look a little\nforeign to you, but this looks really\nnice for what I'm building out. It\nmatches it perfectly. You can now take\nthis design system including all the\nassets you built, all of that, hit\nshare, and then you can say, \"Hand this\noff to Claude Code.\" So if you're\nbuilding your app now in Claude Code,\nyou just hand this off to it, and it now\nhas the full dashboard and can take all\nof this and implement it into your app.\nYou now went from having AI slop to a\nfully designed, professionally built out\ndesign system exactly to your liking. If\nyou want to take it further and you want\nto refine it from here, edit things, you\ncan do that. You can go into your chat,\nsay, change this, make this better,\nchange this color, I like this, I don't\nlike this, and make it even better for\nyour taste. This is the system you need\nto be using. Combining Chad GPT image\ngen, which is bestin-class and has\nbasically no limits whatsoever. using\nthat for your exploration, refinement,\nmoving it over to claw design so you can\noneshot build out some incredible\ndesigns. This is claw design and if you\nlearned anything at all, hit like down\nbelow. I'm going to do an entire\nworkshop on this and build this out live\nand take all your questions inside the\nVibe Coding Academy. Make sure to hit\nthe link for that down below. It's the\nnumber one community in AI on planet\nEarth. You'll learn a ton. You'll master\nclaw code, claw design, open claw, all\nthat. Hit the link down there. Subscribe\nand turn on notifications if you haven't\nalready. All I do is make amazing videos\nabout AI. I live stream Monday,\nWednesday, Friday, 11 a.m. Pacific. So,\ntune in for that as well. I hope you\nlearned something here. I'm so eternally\ngrateful you would spend your time with\nme and listen to my advice and hang out\nwith me. It really means the world.\nThank you so much. I love you all and\nI'll talk to you\n\n2.8s · 23m 48s YouTube · 5.0k words · text via transcript/captionTracks","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-rex"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777347554479}}
{"type":"message","id":"cbaef368","parentId":"a94bc942","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:40:45.615Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Got the transcript for video 2. Now let me save it to a file.","thinkingSignature":"f32d2383bdb37e2c7f99235ca4d9ea30cb184de4413bfff5ae32f6323bf68dbe"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it. Saving video 2.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_om9013y2365c_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/SecondBrain/Research/alex-finn/2026-04-27/2026-04-27 - The Best Claude Design Workflow - Alex Finn.md","content":"# The Best Claude Design Workflow You'll Ever See\n\n**Channel:** Alex Finn  \n**Date:** 2026-04-27  \n**Original Video:** https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_v_heNg0j1c  \n**Duration:** 23 minutes 48 seconds  \n**Views:** 19K  \n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nAlex Finn reveals a system for creating professional-level app designs by combining **ChatGPT's image gen model** (for exploration/refinement) with **Claude Design** (for final design system and prototype generation). The core insight: Claude Design has extremely low usage limits, so do all your experimentation and exploration in ChatGPT (which has high/almost unlimited limits), then bring your refined direction to Claude Design for a single, focused, one-shot design system.\n\n### The 4-Stage System\n\n**On the ChatGPT Side:**\n\n1. **Stage 1 — Inspiration:** Browse X/Twitter for logos and designs you like. Bookmark/screenshot 4-5 images as inspiration. Paste them into ChatGPT.\n2. **Stage 2 — Exploration:** Ask ChatGPT to generate a sheet of logos based on your inspiration. Pick 1-2 you like. Screenshot them and ask for variations.\n3. **Stage 3 — Refinement (repeat 5-6 times):** Keep selecting elements you like from each batch, ask for more variations. Each refinement is one micro-step toward your final direction. Allows the model to get creative and go \"outside the box\" too.\n4. **Stage 4 — Branding Guide:** Once you have your logo and color direction, ask ChatGPT to design a full branding guide (colors, typography, logo variations, merch concepts) using its image gen model.\n\nThen ask ChatGPT to write you a detailed prompt for Claude Design.\n\n**On the Claude Design Side:**\n\n1. **Upload your assets** (the final logo/branding sheet from ChatGPT) and paste the prompt ChatGPT wrote.\n2. **Generate design system** — Claude reviews your code (if you have a GitHub repo), sets up all brand assets, colors, typography, UI kit components. Takes ~5 minutes.\n3. **Review & refine** — Rate each component (colors, fonts, buttons, etc.) and make adjustments.\n4. **Build prototype** — Create a high-fidelity prototype (e.g., dashboard) using the design system.\n5. **Hand off to Claude Code** — Share the design system and prototype to hand off to Claude Code for implementation.\n\n### Key Takeaways\n\n- **Why this works:** ChatGPT has near-unlimited usage even on free tier. Claude Design gives you 2-3 uses before hitting weekly limits. Do ALL experimentation on ChatGPT, use Claude Design only for the final one-shot build.\n- **ChatGPT writes better prompts** than humans — let it write the prompt for Claude Design.\n- **Result:** Go from AI slop to a fully designed, professional design system exactly to your taste, with almost no limits frustration.\n\n---\n\n## Full Transcript\n\nI figured out a system that allows you to design the most beautiful apps you can possibly imagine using claw design and Chad GBT's new image gen model. The system I'm about to show you I haven't seen anywhere else on YouTube. When you combine these two tools, even if you have zero design or artistic skills like me, you can create the most beautiful apps, branding designs you've ever made in your life. In this video, I'll go over both these tools, both Claw Design and the new Chad GBT image model. I'll go over how they work, and I'll go through my new system that allows you to combine the two to make the most beautiful designs ever. If you stick with me until the end of the video, you will become a world-class designer. Now, let's lock in and get into it. Now, for those who don't know, over the last week, both Anthropic and OpenAI released two best-in-class tools. Anthropic released Clawude Design, which we'll go through fully, a really amazing design tool. And then Chad GBT released their new image gen model, their second generation image gen model, which is by far the best image gen model out there. It blows Nano Banana out of the water. But there are some challenges with each, though. There's some ways that both have weaknesses, and when you combine them together, their weaknesses go away, and they're amazing. The main challenge is, and we'll go through building some designs in a second with design and the image genen model, claw design's amazing, but much like all the other anthropic products, it has really low usage limits. A lot of people ran into this where they try to build a couple designs and by the end of the second design they made, their limits were gone and had to wait an entire week. The issue with the image gen model is there's no design tools out of the box with it. It only creates images you ask for. It's not great at building entire design kits, but it's absolutely amazing at generating images. It's also incredibly inexpensive and you can even use it on the free tier. When combined, it solves each other's weaknesses. The issue with claw design is because of its low limits. If you've never designed things before, if you're anything like me, I've never designed anything in my life. I'm very unartic. I stink at all of that. When I went into claw design, I had to experiment a ton. I had to like ask questions, try things like 10 different times. I hit my limits without creating anything amazing. When I started combining it though with Chad GBT's image gen model, amazing things happen. Let me show you how this works. So, with each tool, we're going to go through four stages in this system. By going through all these stages, you'll not only have way better results, incredible professional level designs, but you also save tons of money because you're not going to keep hitting your claw limits over and over again. So, let's start off on the Chad GBT image side. We're going to start with inspiration. By the end of these eight stages, you'll have a fully working design system prototype for an app that's going to look incredible and that's going to match exactly what you want. So, stage one is inspiration. We're going to start off on the Chad GBT image side. Our goal of using this new image gen model with Chad GBT is to come up with a logo and design guidelines. This is going to be the base of everything we use in claw design. This is going to allow it so we don't have to experiment a ton in claw design. This will be great cuz we can move all this over after. And then claw design can spit us out an incredible design system and prototype in one go. No experimentation needed. So we don't have to hit our limits. So to come up with our logo and design guidelines, the first thing we need to do is find inspiration and give it to chat GBT. So we have a starting point. This doesn't need to be perfect. just find some images out there that you enjoy, that you like, that you want to use as inspiration and then we'll start doing some exploration so we can make it our own. My favorite way to find inspiration if you don't know where to start is I just like scrolling X. So I go down X and I just look for images and logos I like. So I'll go down, I'll look at images and logos like, \"Oh, I like this. I like this gradient right here.\" So what I'll do is I'll bookmark this. And what I do is I add it to a visual inspiration folder. So I go there. That's now in that folder. I keep going down and I just look for logos and images that I would like to use inside my design system. Oo, I kind of like this Orlando Magic logo. It's nice, simple, clean. I like that. I'm just actually going to save this image. Let's copy this image first of all, even though I'm a Celtics fan. We'll take that logo. I like the way it looks. So I paste that in. I'm scrolling down. Oo, I kind of like these logos. Look at I like the way those look. So let's do this. Let's screenshot this. If you're on Mac, you can do command control shift4. That allows you to kind of copy paste that over. And we put in a few images that we want to use as inspiration. I really like these guys logos. If I knew how to pronounce their name, I'd say is it noose research? Is it Nois Research? I don't know. I like their logo. Let's copy that as well. And now we have in a few pieces of inspiration. You probably want to get to four or five. That's going to be a sweet spot. We're going to do just these three for the sake of this demo here. Now, what we're going to want to do is we're going to take this inspiration and we're going to start doing some exploration. We're going to have it generate us some logos, see what feels good. Take an element here, take an element there, and start getting closer and closer to a final design guideline. So, you're going to want to do this, and this works great if you want to do this alongside with me. Once you put your logos in, you're going to want to describe what you're building at the moment. So, I'm building an app called Henry Intelligent Machines. I'm going to describe what that is and I'm going to say I want to start figuring out a design system and logo for this app. So go in, start describing what you're building. So here's what I said. I'm building an app called Henry Intelligent Machines. It is an AI agent autonomously builds businesses for the user and generates revenue. It can build many businesses at once. Please use the images attached as inspiration. Help me generate a sheet of logos I could potentially choose from. I like octopi and owls. Make different versions with those animals. use your new image gen model. This is an 