{"type":"message","id":"d2b77f3f","parentId":"485c7cac","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:42:24.488Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me read the summarize skill to understand how to use it.","thinkingSignature":"fc7ce4b6a08269d5abe710db09ab3bed98b2294bd5aa0b660a838222c1fd032c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9rvojwf2nge7_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/summarize/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6663,"output":57,"cacheRead":27269,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33989,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777347420898,"responseId":"063f5e5de3ce1e29ff9cb36888741d92"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9850d93e","parentId":"d2b77f3f","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:42:24.488Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9rvojwf2nge7_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: summarize\ndescription: Summarize or transcribe URLs, YouTube/videos, podcasts, articles, transcripts, PDFs, and local files.\nhomepage: https://summarize.sh\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\":\n      {\n        \"emoji\": \"🧾\",\n        \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"summarize\"] },\n        \"install\":\n          [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"brew\",\n              \"kind\": \"brew\",\n              \"formula\": \"steipete/tap/summarize\",\n              \"bins\": [\"summarize\"],\n              \"label\": \"Install summarize (brew)\",\n            },\n          ],\n      },\n  }\n---\n\n# Summarize\n\nFast CLI to summarize URLs, local files, and YouTube links.\n\n## When to use (trigger phrases)\n\nUse this skill immediately when the user asks any of:\n\n- “use summarize.sh”\n- “what’s this link/video about?”\n- “summarize this URL/article”\n- “transcribe this YouTube/video” (best-effort transcript extraction; no `yt-dlp` needed)\n\n## Quick start\n\n```bash\nsummarize \"https://example.com\" --model google/gemini-3-flash-preview\nsummarize \"/path/to/file.pdf\" --model google/gemini-3-flash-preview\nsummarize \"https://youtu.be/dQw4w9WgXcQ\" --youtube auto\n```\n\n## YouTube: summary vs transcript\n\nBest-effort transcript (URLs only):\n\n```bash\nsummarize \"https://youtu.be/dQw4w9WgXcQ\" --youtube auto --extract-only\n```\n\nIf the user asked for a transcript but it’s huge, return a tight summary first, then ask which section/time range to expand.\n\n## Model + keys\n\nSet the API key for your chosen provider:\n\n- OpenAI: `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n- Anthropic: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`\n- xAI: `XAI_API_KEY`\n- Google: `GEMINI_API_KEY` (aliases: `GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY`, `GOOGLE_API_KEY`)\n\nDefault model is `google/gemini-3-flash-preview` if none is set.\n\n## Useful flags\n\n- `--length short|medium|long|xl|xxl|<chars>`\n- `--max-output-tokens <count>`\n- `--extract-only` (URLs only)\n- `--json` (machine readable)\n- `--firecrawl auto|off|always` (fallback extraction)\n- `--youtube auto` (Apify fallback if `APIFY_API_TOKEN` set)\n\n## Config\n\nOptional config file: `~/.summarize/config.json`\n\n```json\n{ \"model\": \"openai/gpt-5.2\" }\n```\n\nOptional services:\n\n- `FIRECRAWL_API_KEY` for blocked sites\n- `APIFY_API_TOKEN` for YouTube fallback\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777347423453}}
{"type":"message","id":"0b7e8045","parentId":"9850d93e","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:42:24.488Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I know how to use the summarize tool. Let me transcribe the first video. The video URL is `https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cgp-gfSbmNE`.\n\nI'll use `summarize \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cgp-gfSbmNE\" --youtube auto --extract-only` to get the transcript.\n\nLet me start with the first video.","thinkingSignature":"731fb744e331db62788097f26919cb8f1ecff9db7705cee089bd7ae8ef019d6a"},{"type":"text","text":"Starting on video 1: **\"ChatGPT 5.5 Codex: I can't believe they did this...\"**\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nt21muk4pak4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"summarize \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cgp-gfSbmNE\" --youtube auto --extract-only","timeout":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":7331,"output":162,"cacheRead":27269,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34762,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777347423455,"responseId":"063f5e5f15c7d6ca0512bc868ab1d78b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"bdd7e43c","parentId":"0b7e8045","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:42:24.488Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nt21muk4pak4_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Transcript:\nI've been using Chat GPT 5.5 non-stop\nsince it released a few days ago and I'm\nblown away. I figured out a workflow\nthat I'm going to show you in this video\nthat I don't think I've seen anywhere\nelse that will completely change how you\nbuild with AI. I also put it\nhead-to-head with Opus 47 and Claude\ncode in hundreds of tests and I can\nconfidently tell you one of these two\nare better than the other. In this\nvideo, I'll go over what makes Chat GPT\n5.5 so different, why the Codex app is a\ncomplete game-changer, show you my\nmaster workflow for both beginners and\nadvanced, then tell you what you should\nbe using once and for all, Opus 47 and\nClaude code or Chat GPT 5.5 and Codex.\nThis is going to be a banger. Let's lock\nin and get into it. This isn't a channel\nwhere we spend 20 minutes reading blog\nposts, looking at charts, and looking at\nfake benchmark tests. No, we're not\ndoing that. We get straight into the\naction. So, this is Codex. This is the\ndesktop Codex app. This is by far the\nbest way to be using Chat GPT 5.5. I\nbasically spend 90% of my day now inside\nof this app. So, what you need to do\nimmediately is go and download this.\nThey have released so many updates over\nthe last few days to this. It is\nbasically a completely different app.\nSo, if you haven't downloaded and used\nCodex for desktop yet, go ahead, pause\nthis video, do it now. So, everything we\ndo, you can do it with me together. So,\nreal quick, we'll talk about the big\nimprovements I've experienced in Chat\nGPT 5.5. Number one, and this is the\nbiggest improvement in my eyes, takes\naction by default. Chat GPT 5.4, the\nbiggest issue is I tell it to do\nsomething, it doesn't actually do it. I\nhave to sit there and beg on my knees,\n\"Please, Chat GPT 5.4, do what I tell\nyou to do.\" And it wouldn't do it. It\nwas very smart, but not about that\naction. 5.5, slightly less chatty. I\nfelt like I was reading a novel every\ntime I would give 5.4 a prompt. I\nliterally would crash out sometimes and\nsay, \"Please, for the love of God, just\nstop saying so much. Get straight to the\npoint.\" That is not as much of an issue\nwith 5.5. Still a little bit of an\nissue, not as much of an issue. Better\npersonality. 5.4 was a cold Terminator\nmachine. It did not feel warm to talk\nto. It was not quite as fun to talk to.\n5.5, better personality. Not perfect\npersonality, better personality. And a\nbig one here, it is significantly\nsmarter. It creates excellent,\nexcellent, excellent code. I basically,\nover the last few days of testing this,\nhave gotten zero bugs out of the code\nit's written. Zero, zero, zero. So, it\nis much, much, much smarter, which is\namazing to see. Now, these are all big,\ngreat improvements, but I'll tell you\nwhat, the biggest improvement comes from\nthe experience of using it inside this\napp I'm showing you here. This is the\nnew Codex desktop app. You need to do\nyourself a favor. You need to pause this\nvideo immediately. You need to go\ndownload this. Go download the Codex\ndesktop app because this is incredible.\nThis is where I've spent 95% of my\nwaking moments over the last few days is\ninside this app. There are 20,000\ndifferent features that make it amazing\nthat I'll be going through in this\nvideo, but you need to be downloading\nthis immediately. 5.5 with this Codex\napp is\nIt's a match made in heaven. It's a\nbeautiful It's a beautiful harmony of AI\ngenius. So, here's the plan for the\nvideo and here's why you need to buckle\nin immediately. I'm going to build out a\nbasic app using this Codex app. I'm\ngoing to show you how to use it, many\nthe incredible features. Once we got a\ngood feel for the app, we're comfortable\nwith it, we know what it's doing, then