{"type":"message","id":"53fccef1","parentId":"bdd7e43c","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:42:24.488Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Got the transcript. Now let me create the file for this first video. I'll save it to the folder with today's date.\n\nFile name: `2026-04-27 - ChatGPT 5.5 Codex - Alex Finn.md`\n\nLet me create a nicely formatted file with the transcript and summary.","thinkingSignature":"93db7eb560a3ce96da083750d276a5aa15c51e39e9dcf22d0b7bdaef05bd437a"},{"type":"text","text":"Got the transcript. Saving video 1 now.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0p81tegkwzqv_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/SecondBrain/Research/alex-finn/2026-04-27/2026-04-27 - ChatGPT 5.5 Codex - Alex Finn.md","content":"# ChatGPT 5.5 Codex: I Can't Believe They Did This...\n\n**Channel:** Alex Finn  \n**Date:** 2026-04-27  \n**Original Video:** https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cgp-gfSbmNE  \n**Duration:** 30 minutes 32 seconds  \n**Views:** 51K  \n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nAlex Finn reviews ChatGPT 5.5 combined with the Codex desktop app and compares it head-to-head with Opus 4.7 and Claude Code.\n\n### Key Highlights\n\n**ChatGPT 5.5 Improvements:**\n- Takes action by default (vs 5.4 which required begging)\n- Less verbose, more direct\n- Better personality, warmer to talk to\n- Significantly smarter — near-zero bugs in generated code\n- Integrated image gen model (gpt-image-1) is \"not even close\" to the best\n\n**Codex Desktop App — The Real Game-Changer:**\n- Download immediately — it's been completely updated\n- Built-in browser for live app testing\n- **Computer use** — Codex controls your actual computer to test apps autonomously\n- **Annotation** — click directly on UI elements to edit them rather than prompting back and forth\n- Multi-chat multitasking within projects\n- Chat section + coding section combined (vs Claude's separated interfaces)\n- Image gen model deeply integrated — generate UI mockups before building\n\n**Advanced Workflow — Linear Integration:**\n- Use **Linear** (free) as a project management \"second brain\" for Codex\n- Codex creates and manages tasks (issues) in Linear automatically\n- Enables multiple agents to work off the same task board simultaneously\n- Transform from one agent doing everything → multi-agent collaboration\n\n**Head-to-Head: ChatGPT 5.5 + Codex vs Opus 4.7 + Claude Code**\n\n| | ChatGPT 5.5 + Codex | Opus 4.7 + Claude Code |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Model Intelligence** | ✅ Wins — consistent, doesn't get stupider over time | ❌ Declines after ~1 week |\n| **Limits** | ✅ Way higher, resets frequently | ❌ Getting lower |\n| **Default UI Quality** | ❌ Still feels like \"slop\" | ✅ Wins |\n| **Personality** | ❌ Gap closed but still behind | ✅ Warmer, more fun |\n| **Action/Taking Initiative** | ✅ Major improvement | ✅ Still crawls when blocked |\n| **Mobile App** | ❌ Coming soon | ✅ Available |\n| **Image Gen Integration** | ✅ Best in world, built-in | ❌ None |\n| **Computer Use** | ✅ Available | ❌ None |\n| **Integrations (Linear, etc.)** | ✅ Deep integrations | ❌ Limited |\n\n**Verdict:** ChatGPT 5.5 + Codex wins for coding. Alex switched his workflow permanently — higher limits, smarter model, better integrations, computer use. The one remaining Claude strengths: better default UIs, slightly better personality.\n\n**Note:** Alex mentions doing a separate follow-up on OpenClaw — whether to use Claude or ChatGPT with OpenClaw specifically.\n\n---\n\n## Full Transcript\n\nI've been using Chat GPT 5.5 non-stop since it released a few days ago and I'm blown away. I figured out a workflow that I'm going to show you in this video that I don't think I've seen anywhere else that will completely change how you build with AI. I also put it head-to-head with Opus 47 and Claude code in hundreds of tests and I can confidently tell you one of these two are better than the other. In this video, I'll go over what makes Chat GPT 5.5 so different, why the Codex app is a complete game-changer, show you my master workflow for both beginners and advanced, then tell you what you should be using once and for all, Opus 47 and Claude code or Chat GPT 5.5 and Codex. This is going to be a banger. Let's lock in and get into it. This isn't a channel where we spend 20 minutes reading blog posts, looking at charts, and looking at fake benchmark tests. No, we're not doing that. We get straight into the action. So, this is Codex. This is the desktop Codex app. This is by far the best way to be using Chat GPT 5.5. I basically spend 90% of my day now inside of this app. So, what you need to do immediately is go and download this. They have released so many updates over the last few days to this. It is basically a completely different app. So, if you haven't downloaded and used Codex for desktop yet, go ahead, pause this video, do it now. So, everything we do, you can do it with me together. So, real quick, we'll talk about the big improvements I've experienced in Chat GPT 5.5. Number one, and this is the biggest improvement in my eyes, takes action by default. Chat GPT 5.4, the biggest issue is I tell it to do something, it doesn't actually do it. I have to sit there and beg on my knees, \"Please, Chat GPT 5.4, do what I tell you to do.\" And it wouldn't do it. It was very smart, but not about that action. 5.5, slightly less chatty. I felt like I was reading a novel every time I would give 5.4 a prompt. I literally would crash out sometimes and say, \"Please, for the love of God, just stop saying so much. Get straight to the point.\" That is not as much of an issue with 5.5. Still a little bit of an issue, not as much of an issue. Better personality. 5.4 was a cold Terminator machine. It did not feel warm to talk to. It was not quite as fun to talk to. 5.5, better personality. Not perfect personality, better personality. And a big one here, it is significantly smarter. It creates excellent, excellent, excellent code. I basically, over the last few days of testing this, have gotten zero bugs out of the code it's written. Zero, zero, zero. So, it is much, much, much smarter, which is amazing to see. Now, these are all big, great improvements, but I'll tell you what, the biggest improvement comes from the experience of using it inside this app I'm showing you here. This is the new Codex desktop app. You need to do yourself a favor. You need to pause this video immediately. You need to go download this. Go download the Codex desktop app because this is incredible. This is where I've spent 95% of my waking moments over the last few days is inside this app. There are 20,000 different features that make it amazing that I'll be going through in this video, but you need to be downloading this immediately. 5.5 with this Codex app is a match made in heaven. It's a beautiful harmony of AI genius. So, here's the plan for the video and here's why you need to buckle in immediately. I'm going to build out a basic app using this Codex app. I'm going to show you how to use it, many the incredible features. Once we got a good feel for the app, we're comfortable with it, we know what it's doing, then we'll go to a super advanced workflow that I promise will change your life. It has changed everything for me. It's helped me build apps literally, I'm not even joking, 10 times better and faster. We'll go into that advanced workflow right after we get comfortable with this and I go through the strengths of the model and the app. When we talk about Chat GPT 5.5, we're also implicitly talking about this app as well just because they work so well together. So, getting off a few things, let's just do quick tour of the app. We'll spend a couple seconds here. Over on the left-hand side, everything is organized by project. You'll see a lot of new project 1 2 3 4 5 over here. That's cuz I've been doing insane amounts of tests over the last few days. But, what's great is is you can multitask so easily in here. You can start off multiple chats in a project, work on the back end while you're working on the front end, while you have a chat going where you're game planning the entire app itself. This is a beautiful part about the Codex app. Then down below, what's amazing is you can also have chats. So, they've combined into this super app not only the coding section, but also you have a chat section. For those who build things, you need to be having chats separate from your building, separate from your coding. So, as one goes at it, as you're coding and building something, you can have a chat going where you're doing high-level planning, design, development, whatever it is, you can have those separate chats going. So, you can strategize and brainstorm on the app and business you're building. So, it's beautiful they combined this all in one. In the Claude app, it's very different. Everything is separated out. So, you have your chats and then you have to go over here and you switch to your code. And to talk to one or the other, you're switching between these entirely different interfaces. You can see even the colors of the background are different. It's just completely different app. I don't like that separation quite as much. With Codex, it is all tightly integrated, which is beautiful. One thing you also want to do before you start building is go into settings down here. Go into your settings. Go over to computer use and make sure this is turned on. For me, it was off by default. Make sure you turn this on. This is one of the new amazing features that they just dropped in here where it can control your entire computer. It's clear they're trying to eat open claw and put it into this Codex app. I'm fine with it. You just got to make sure you turn on this computer use right here, which will allow Codex to do a lot of really cool things, including testing your apps, doing different things on your computer. It's all part of the super app they're going for. So, let's do this. Let's