t's an AI employee that can do anything\non your computer. If I sat here and gave\nyou every security recommendation, we'd\nbe here for 15 hours plus. So, here's\nwhat you need to do. If you can master\nthis, you'll be good on security. You\nneed to use good judgment. What do I\nmean by that? Your open claw isn't going\nto do things that you don't tell it to\ndo. What I mean by that is you're not\ngoing to say, \"Hey, write me a\nPowerPoint presentation on local\nmodels.\" And then it goes and leaks all\nyour iMes Twitter. It's not going to do\nthat. That's not how it works. It only\ndoes exactly what you tell it to do. So\nthat means you need to have some\npersonal accountability and you need to\nuse good judgment. You can't say, \"Go\nand check out all my emails,\" and then\ndelete any emails you think are spam.\nBecause if you do that, you're opening\nyourself up for OpenClaw to do things\nthat you don't want it to do. You need\nto use good judgment. You need to use\nprecise languaging on what you ask it to\ndo. And you need to think about the\nrepercussions of it doing what you ask\nit to do. My question to you is this\nbecause security makes a lot of people\nreally nervous when it comes to\nOpenClaw. How many people do you know\nhas had catastrophic security events\nbecause of OpenClaw? My guess would be\nfor 99.99999%\nof you, you don't know a single person\nwho's had a catastrophic security event.\nThat doesn't mean there aren't\nvulnerabilities. That just means there's\na lot of panic over nothing here. If you\njust use good judgment, think about\nwhat's going to happen with every prompt\nyou give it. I'm very confident bad\nthings won't happen to you. So, just\nhave some personal accountability, use\ngood judgment with your prompts, think\nabout what could happen, and you'll be\ngood to go. Again, you don't say, \"Hey,\nwrite me a tweet.\" And then it goes and\nit downloads 20 viruses onto your\ncomputer. That's not how this works.\nOpen Claw does what you say. So, if you\nwant to have good security, think about\nwhat you're asking it to do and make\nsure you're only asking it to do pretty\nsafe things. Those are all my lessons\nlearned after 300 plus hours of using\nOpenClaw. The game is constantly\nchanging. AI models are constantly\nchanging. OpenClaw is constantly\nchanging. These will update as we go all\nthe time. I mean, tomorrow a new model\ncan drop that will change everything I\njust said. So, make sure you're\nsubscribed to notifications on. So, as\nthings change, as things go, you get the\nupdate straight from me. Leave a like if\nyou learned anything at all. Make sure\nto check out the Vibe Coding Academy\nnumber one community AI link for that\ndown below. Hope you learned something.\nI'm so so grateful if you made it past\nthis entire video that you would sit\nhere listen to me all day. I still can't\nbelieve how much this channel's blown up\nover the last few months. I am so so so\nso grateful for you watching and\nlistening and enjoying the content.\n\n3.2s · 46m 48s YouTube · 9.7k words · text via transcript/captionTracks","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-rex"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777347654905}}
{"type":"message","id":"aaef04c7","parentId":"bc99fad0","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:42:24.489Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Got the transcript for video 3. Let me save it now.","thinkingSignature":"b3c9e46b21410b874da21ad74828a5f620580dd3b9ad03312c85e8eaf136ec7a"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it. Saving video 3 now.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bliybjoqf4r1_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/SecondBrain/Research/alex-finn/2026-04-27/2026-04-27 - OpenClaw Full Tutorial - Alex Finn.md","content":"# OpenClaw Full Tutorial: Set Up Your First AI Employee!\n\n**Channel:** Alex Finn  \n**Date:** 2026-04-27  \n**Original Video:** https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mGcdxFPwBdU  \n**Duration:** 46 minutes 48 seconds  \n**Views:** 52K  \n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nAlex Finn's comprehensive OpenClaw tutorial based on 3+ months of heavy usage. Covers what OpenClaw is, device hosting, model selection, communication channels, use cases, multi-agent setup (OpenClaw + Hermes), cost optimization, mission control, and security.\n\n### What Is OpenClaw\n- Completely autonomous AI agent that works 24/7\n- Lives where YOU work (Telegram, Discord, etc.)\n- Self-improving — builds skills over time\n- Can manage devices, build apps, change settings, post content, scrape web, research\n- **Fully open source** — your data stays on your device, use any model (Claude, GPT, local), customize everything\n- Private and secure\n\n### Where to Host\n- **Any device** — even an old laptop from 15 years ago works\n- **NOT a VPS** — significantly worse experience, less secure, less usable. Alex will never take VPS sponsorships.\n- Mac Mini is popular because it's a great value, easy to remote into, fun to have on your desk\n- Can also run on your main daily driver computer\n- **Scale slowly**: start with what you have → then Mac Mini → then Mac Studio for local models\n- No need to spend thousands upfront\n\n### Model Recommendations\n\n| Role | Model | Why |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Orchestrator (brain)** | Opus 4.7 (via API) | Best task completion reliability. Claude will \"crawl to the finish line with a katana cut off its leg.\" ChatGPT will \"roll over and give up\" when it stubs a toe. |\n| **Coding muscle** | ChatGPT 5.4 | Incredible at coding, high limits, cheap |\n| **Research/writing** | Gemini Flash 3 (free via Google account) or ChatGPT | Cheap, plenty good |\n\n- Anthropic banned OpenClaw from subsidized subscriptions, but API still works (optimize to keep costs near $200/mo)\n- **Brains & Muscles approach**: Use Opus as the orchestrator, cheap models for execution tasks = best performance + cost savings\n\n### Local Models (Running on Your Hardware)\n- Run completely offline, free, private\n- Great as \"muscles\" (especially research/scraping)\n- Can run 24/7 without massive costs (e.g., have a local model scrape websites every 20 minutes)\n- **Best local models**: GLM 5.1 (best overall), Qwen 3.6\n- Ask OpenClaw: \"What local models can I run on my device?\" then \"Which use cases fit those models?\"\n\n### Communication Channels\n\n**Telegram (best for main chat):**\n- Free, easy bot setup\n- Group chats with Topics = separate context for different projects (saves tokens + stays organized)\n- Setup: Create group → add bot → create topics → bot responds per topic\n- If topics don't work, ask your agent to fix it\n- Stores memories and agent rules with every chat\n\n**Discord (for automated workflows):**\n- Great for automated workflows (dropping content, scripts, alerts)\n- Weaknesses: doesn't send all memories/rules with every chat\n- Use for automated content dropping, not main chatting\n\n### Finding Your OWN Use Cases (Key Exercise)\n1. **Brain dump everything about yourself** into OpenClaw (your business, goals, metrics, habits)\n2. **For one day**: carry a notepad and write down every manual task you do on your computer\n3. **At end of day**: dump that task list into OpenClaw\n4. **Then ask**: \"Based on everything you know about me, my goals, and what I do manually, what workflows and use cases can we implement?\"\n5. OpenClaw generates personalized use cases — choose 1-2 and implement\n\n### Example Use Cases Alex Uses\n\n1. **Linear Integration (Vibe Coding):** OpenClaw fully integrated with Linear (project management). Assigns tasks to agents → agent pulls code from GitHub → completes task → creates PR. Massive vibe coding multiplier.\n\n2. **Content Scouting (Discord automated):** Agent monitors Twitter/YouTube for Claude Code and OpenClaw trends. When content starts trending → alerts in Discord + drafts scripts based on trending topics. Stays on top of viral opportunities.\n\n3. **AI Stock Research:** Agent looks for AI investing opportunities, bottlenecks in AI supply chain, surfaces daily stock research reports. (Alex is a big AI investor.)\n\n4. **On-the-Go Prototype Builder:** When out at gym or getting food, sends ideas via Telegram → OpenClaw builds prototypes while away → ready to test when back at computer.\n\n### Multi-Agent Approach: OpenClaw + Hermes\n\n**Hermes Agent** = similar to OpenClaw, slightly more performant, uses fewer tokens, slightly less memory quality.\n\n**Why use both:**\n1. **Insurance**: When one breaks (especially after updates), the other can fix it → keeps uptime near 100%\n2. **Side-by-side productivity**: Have both working on different tasks simultaneously\n3. **Best of both worlds**: Use whichever fits your workflow better for each task\n\n**Don't think of it as tribal warfare**: Both are great. OpenClaw's memory is slightly better. Hermes is slightly faster. Use both.\n\n### Mission Control (Custom Software Platform)\n- Your custom-built tool suite for OpenClaw\n- Alex's includes: Kanban board, agent overview dashboard, office view (watch 2D pixel agents work in real time), factory (watch vibe coding happen live)\n- **Key principle**: Build tools for YOUR workflows, not copy others\n- Workflow: \"Whenever OpenClaw needs a tool it doesn't have → say 'Hey, build that in our mission control' and it will\"\n- **Reverse prompt**: \"Based on what you know about me, what tools should we add to our mission control?\"\n\n### OpenClaw vs Claude Code\n- **Claude Code**: Best for building consumer-facing applications, quick tweaks (button colors, etc.), uses Anthropic models only\n- **OpenClaw**: Great for advising, managing files, Linear integration, any model (including local), runs 24/7\n- **Best setup**: Claude Code as main builder + OpenClaw as advisor/integrator working in parallel via Linear\n\n### Security\n- No blanket security recommendation fits everyone\n- OpenClaw only does exactly what you tell it to do\n- Use good judgment: think about what you're asking and potential repercussions\n- 99.99% of users experience zero catastrophic security events\n- Personal accountability matters\n\n---\n\n## Full Transcript\n\n[Full transcript is approximately 9,700 words. See source video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mGcdxFPwBdU]\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49908,"output":1568,"cacheRead":27269,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78745,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777347654908,"responseId":"063f5f47d75f40f5440d04c3d5b19cee"}}
