pears. So for instance, I\nhave this Alex Finn wiki which is\nbasically a place all my memories get\nstored that I can visually explore. So\ninstead of having to go into Obsidian, I\ncan go in here. I can see what people\nare stored in my memories, what concepts\nare stored in my memories, what sources\nare stored in my memories, things like\nthat, and be able to easily explore\nthings I've talked about in the past. So\nyou can have things like your own\npersonal wiki. All I did for this was I\nwent to my open client and said, \"Hey,\nbuild a visual interface for our\nmemories.\" almost like a personal wiki\nand it went and built this. So, so many\nother really, really cool things you can\ndo once you start building this personal\nmemory system inside of Obsidian. The\npossibilities really are endless. A lot\nmore coming soon. So, make sure to\nsubscribe and turn notifications. I drop\na lot of these prompts and stuff as I\ncome up with them inside the Vibe Coding\nAcademy. So, make sure to sign up for\nthat if you're interested. Also, let me\nknow down below what you want me to talk\nabout next. You want me to go more into\nhardware and local models when it comes\nto these agents? Do you want me to talk\nabout more about use cases and workflows\nor more about improving your agent like\nwe just did in this video? Let me know\ndown below. I'm very interested. All my\nvideos are based on your feedback. I\nhope this was helpful. I'll see you in\nthe next video.\n\n2.5s · 10m 58s YouTube · 2.3k words · text via transcript/captionTracks","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-rex"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777347744480}}
{"type":"compaction","id":"50d37200","parentId":"621f9d5d","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:42:49.426Z","summary":"\n\n## Goal\nTranscribe and summarize all recent YouTube videos from Alex Finn's channel (@AlexFinnOfficial), stopping after completing a specific video. Save each video's transcription/summary as a separate file in a date-stamped folder.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- One file per video (transcription + summary combined)\n- Folder/filename date: 2026-04-27\n- Save location: `~/Desktop/SecondBrain/Research/alex-finn/2026-04-27/`\n- Process most recent videos first, working backward\n- Stop after completing: https://youtu.be/Qkqe-uRhQJE\n- (none)\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Confirmed task scope and constraints with Bobby\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Awaiting final confirmation to start\n\n### Blocked\n- (none)\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Use `summarize` skill**: Available skill that handles YouTube video transcription and summarization\n- **Process in reverse chronological order**: Start from most recent, stop at specified video\n- **Single file per video**: Transcription + summary combined in one file per video\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Browse to Alex Finn's channel: https://www.youtube.com/@AlexFinnOfficial/videos\n2. Identify the 10 most recent videos (or all until reaching stop video)\n3. For each video (most recent first):\n   - Use `summarize` skill to transcribe and summarize\n   - Save output as single file in `~/Desktop/SecondBrain/Research/alex-finn/2026-04-27/`\n4. Stop after completing: https://youtu.be/Qkqe-uRhQJE\n\n## Critical Context\n- Channel URL: https://www.youtube.com/@AlexFinnOfficial/videos\n- Stop video URL: https://youtu.be/Qkqe-uRhQJE\n- Target folder: `~/Desktop/SecondBrain/Research/alex-finn/2026-04-27/`\n- Assistant inbox check showed pending tasks from Cody (research on Recipe Rip UX/psychology) and DJ (AI music generation research) - neither from Dean\n- Bobby previously asked if Dean sent any tasks (answer: no)\n\n---\n\n**Turn Con