{"type":"message","id":"598fdc11","parentId":"a3cc5aff","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:43:52.740Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Video 4 done. Now back to Video 5, which I already have the transcript for. Let me save that one first, then continue with Video 6.\n","thinkingSignature":"fd3b90453464b668a422dbc2849ac3a7fd134a08c63a985552c29e9bc8774408"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_u8ldfc4lhglf_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Claude Code Desktop Deep Dive\n\n**Channel:** Alex Finn  \n**Date:** 2026-04-27  \n**Original Video:** https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pHr1O_Af5NA  \n**Duration:** ~14 minutes  \n**Views:** 47K  \n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nAlex showcases the new Claude Code desktop app, demonstrating why it's now the best way to vibe code. Key features include project-based session organization, customizable interface, multitasking with multiple agents, co-work mode for non-coding tasks, and a new routines feature for scheduled tasks.\n\n### Key Features\n\n**Project-Based Organization**\n- Sessions organized by project — spin up multiple sessions per project\n- Yellow dots indicate attention needed\n- Easily jump between projects and sessions\n\n**Customizable Interface**\n- Pin different panes: tasks, plan, live browser view, etc.\n- Recommended: keep tasks and plan pinned for visibility\n\n**New Session Types**\n- Local (edits code on your machine)\n- Cloud (runs on Anthropic servers, pulls from GitHub)\n- Remote (use from phone/mobile)\n\n**Best Practice:** Use local for separate features (avoids conflicts), cloud for flexible multi-agent work.\n\n**Tab System**\n- Chat: brainstorming, bouncing ideas\n- Co-work: file management, document work (Alex used this to do taxes in 1 hour — normally takes 10)\n- Code: coding sessions with full session management\n\n**Mode Recommendations**\n- Accept Edits mode for ~95% of work (auto-switches to plan when needed)\n- Verbosity: Normal is perfectly dialed in\n- Use High mode for most tasks (best balance of thinking/speed)\n- Max mode available for most complex tasks\n\n**Press and Hold to Talk** — voice input available for those who prefer talking\n\n**Session Pinning** — pin important sessions (like main driver chats) to top for quick access\n\n**Slash Commands** — now have hover descriptions for clarity\n\n**Routines (NEW FEATURE)**\n- Run tasks on schedule, even when laptop is closed (cloud)\n- Example: Nightly code review at 9 PM — checks all commits, reviews code, fixes bugs\n- Linear Connector: can automatically go into Linear every night and fix bugs\n- Game changer for automated workflows\n\n### Recommended Workflow\n1. Create a session in every project you're working on (pin them)\n2. Start sessions for specific features within each project\n3. Use local for separate features, cloud for similar/complementary work\n4. Use work trees for advanced GitHub users\n\n### Use Cases Shown\n- **Taxes:** Ran all credit card statements through co-work → categorized and organized into spreadsheet in 1 hour (vs 10 hours manual)\n- **Nightly code reviews:** Automated GitHub commit review and bug fixes on a schedule\n- **Linear bug fixing:** Connector runs every night, fixes bugs automatically","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/SecondBrain/Research/alex-finn/2026-04-27/2026-04-27 - Claude Code Desktop Deep Dive - Alex Finn.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":861,"output":699,"cacheRead":44608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46168,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777347806295,"responseId":"063f5fde9a88e7443e08f05efc9859b3"}}
