{"type":"message","id":"5132ca73","parentId":"d6501370","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:45:09.409Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants me to take it one video at a time and start. Let me start with the most recent video and do one at a time. Based on the summary, the most recent video is the OpenClaw Full Tutorial. But wait - the summary says Video 1 and 2 are already done. Let me check what the current state is.\n\nLooking at the summary:\n- Video 1: ChatGPT 5.5 Codex ✅ (saved)\n- Video 2: The Best Claude Design Workflow ✅ (saved)\n- Video 3: OpenClaw Full Tutorial - I just wrote the file (6337 bytes)\n\nBut the summary says Video 3 transcript was retrieved but the turn was truncated before the file could be written. I did write the file though. \n\nNow I need to identify the next video in the sequence. The summary indicates there are more videos after the OpenClaw Full Tutorial, so I should check what comes next.\n","thinkingSignature":"ba451e421a4942d9ed925664df3632dbfbcca1203751390292821c0320cdb564"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGot it Bobby! Let me do this one at a time. Based on our progress:\n\n- ✅ Video 1: ChatGPT 5.5 Codex\n- ✅ Video 2: The Best Claude Design Workflow\n- ✅ Video 3: OpenClaw Full Tutorial (just finished writing)\n\n**Next up: Video 4** — \"Claude Code Secrets + Linear Clone App Build\" (13 min)\n\nLet me save this one now:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_11h27hvgu595_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Claude Code Secrets + Linear Clone App Build\n\n**Channel:** Alex Finn  \n**Date:** 2026-04-27  \n**Original Video:** https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8YhYtIF9PYI  \n**Duration:** 13 minutes 3 seconds  \n**Views:** 38K  \n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nAlex implements 7 secrets revealed by Boris Churinny (Claude Code creator) for getting the most out of Claude Code and Opus 4.7, while building a Linear clone app live.\n\n### The 7 Secrets\n\n1. **Auto Mode (Shift+Shift+Shift)**  \n   - Replaces the constant permissionasking with AI-determined permissions\n   - Allows Claude Code to work continuously for hours without interrupting every 5 seconds\n   - Set as the default mode\n\n2. **Frontload All Information**  \n   - Give Opus all instructions at once at the start of a session\n   - Because it can run autonomously for a long time, stuff everything in upfront\n   - Example prompt below builds a Linear clone in one shot\n\n3. **/recap Command**  \n   - Generates a one-line summary of everything the agent has done\n   - Great for long sessions or after returning the next morning\n   - Essential if treating Claude Code like an employee running for hours\n\n4. **/effort Level Control**  \n   - Extra High and Max modes added\n   - Use Max for the initial big frontloaded prompt\n   - Use Extra High for everything else\n   - Only use High/Medium/Low on lower plans ($20 tier)\n\n5. **Notifications Setup**  \n   - Say \"set up notifications\" and Claude Code creates a skill to ping you when done\n   - After every long-running task, gets notified and can jump back in quickly\n   - Workflow: give long task → switch to chat in desktop app → come back when notification hits\n\n6. **Thinking Budget Control (replaces Extended Thinking)**  \n   - \"Think carefully step by step about this\" = more thinking per micro-step\n   - \"Prioritize responding quickly rather than thinking deeply\" = faster, less tokens\n   - Two knobs: effort (total time on task) + thinking (time per step)\n\n7. **Workflow Integration**  \n   - Use OpenClaw for prototypes on the go (via Telegram) and building tools for agents\n   - Use Claude Code for deep complex consumer-facing apps in coding sessions\n\n### The App Built: Linear Clone\n\nPrompt used:\n> \"I want to build a Linear clone. This should be a project management tool where I can build projects, then put tasks and issues in those projects. Every project, task, and issue should have status and priority. It should be a really clean, simplistic, linear-like interface. I should be able to assign users to each task and add any other features you think will be helpful. Use NextJS to build this out.\"\n\n**Result:** Beautiful Linear clone with projects, tasks, issues, status/priority fields, user assignment, and tags. Fully functional.\n\n### Model Notes\n- Opus 4.7 recommended for orchestrator/building\n- ChatGPT for chatting/bouncing ideas (desktop app)\n- Claude Code desktop app chat mode is now great for Opus\n\n### Resources\n- Vibe Coding Academy: live boot camps Fri, vibe coding sessions Thu\n- Blog post with all tips: linked in Boris's X thread","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/SecondBrain/Research/alex-finn/2026-04-27/2026-04-27 - Claude Code Secrets + Linear Clone - Alex Finn.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":44248,"output":1058,"cacheRead":384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45690,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777347771431,"responseId":"063f5fbb573466dcabaabfc790837bef"}}
